header.gameNote: MVC MEN'S TOURNAMENT - QUARTERFINALS AT ST LOUIS MO

article.headline: Indiana St. 52, Evansville 50
article.story: ST. LOUIS -- Jake Odum hit a pull-up jumper with 0.5 seconds left to lift No. 3 seed Indiana State to a 52-50 win over No. 6 seed Evansville on Friday night in the quarterfinals of the Missouri Valley Conference Tournament. Indiana State (18-13) advances to play No. 2 seed Wichita State in the semifinals Saturday. It's the first time since 2001 the Sycamores reached the semifinals. Colt Ryan led the Purple Aces (15-15) and all scorers with 14 points. The basket by Odum, who led Indiana State with 13 points, was only the second field goal for the Sycamores in the final 9 minutes. A layup by Myles Walker with 1:14 left was the other. Walker was fouled on the basket, and he converted the traditional three-point play to tie the game at 50-50.
